summary: Bayer Leverkusen has maintained their incredible unbeaten streak with a hard-fought 2-2 draw against AS Roma in the second leg of the Europa League semi-final. Thanks to their 2-0 victory in the first leg, the Germans advanced to the Europa League final with a 4-2 aggregate score. Leverkusen's unbeaten run now stands at an astounding 49 matches, making history by equaling the longest unbeaten run in European football. Xabi Alonso's side will now face either Manchester United or Villarreal in the Europa League final on May 18th.

summary: Whooping cough, a highly contagious bacterial infection, is experiencing a resurgence in the United Kingdom. Cases are rising, with hundreds confirmed in Northern Ireland and a potential 40-year peak predicted in 2024. Tragically, five infants have died from the disease this year, prompting health officials to issue an urgent call for vaccination. The decline in vaccination rates has contributed to the outbreak, leaving many vulnerable. Symptoms of whooping cough include a persistent cough, fever, and difficulty breathing, often resembling a whooping sound.

name: Bruce Springsteen
summary: Bruce Springsteen's European tour kicked off in Cardiff, marking the start of a continent-wide musical journey. The legendary musician holds a special connection to Blaenau Gwent, Wales, due to his Irish-Welsh ancestry. Springsteen's performance was met with critical acclaim, with reviewers praising its epic scope and energy. The tour includes a stop in Belfast, where die-hard fans gathered to witness the event live. Traffic updates were issued in Cardiff to accommodate the large crowds attending the concert. A superfan managed to secure a selfie with Springsteen ahead of the Belfast gig. Springsteen expressed his excitement for the upcoming show, promising to deliver an unforgettable performance that would leave the audience energized. The tour schedule includes a performance at the Principality Stadium in Cardiff on May 5, 2024, along with other cities across Europe.
